	<text id="title" x="37" y="35" width="456" height="" autosize="H" style="WIZARD_TITLE" visible="true" fx="SHOW" hidefx="HIDE">
		<content translate="true">Understanding a Child’s Perspective</content>
	</text>
	<text id="material" x="37" y="65" width="697" height="346" autosize="" style="WIZARD_TEXT" visible="true" fx="SHOW" hidefx="HIDE" scroll="AUTO">
		<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Discussion Topic&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;For parents to succeed in communicating with a child, they must understand the child's perspective. The following activity can help parents and caregivers practice seeing situations from a child's point of view.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Discussion Questions&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Ask parents how they would feel in each of the following situations and then compare their responses to how a child might feel in a similar situation.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="32"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="32"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Adult Perspective&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="32"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Starting a new Job&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="32"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Losing your cell phone&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="32"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Being cut off in traffic&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="32"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Meeting a new co-worker&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Sample Feedback &lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Most people appreciate the feeling of being understood, and children are no exception. As a parent strives to understand their child’s perspective and show empathy, both parent and child will feel more connected which will help them build a solid foundation for their relationship.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
	</text>
	<text id="material2" x="270" y="190" width="247" height="100" autosize="" style="WIZARD_TEXT" visible="true" fx="SHOW" hidefx="HIDE" scroll="AUTO">
